rk places these days. ^_^<br><br>For the longest time I had only one source of light: Aegis of Life.  But one day you turn around and look to find rings have a lot more AC than your back item which probably means you need to upgrade it.  I now have a pretty good replacement but now I lack a light giving item which means I'm literially stumbling around in the dark in some places.  I've now carry the Aegis around because I got sick of taking extra time getting oriented in dark zones.<br><br>So a question I have is what are some of the best/better light or vision items out there?  It is possible that I'm stuck with the Aegis but I want to hear from the Humans and Erudites out there on how they fix this problem at this point.<br><br>And no, turning up the gamma isn't a solution! ^_^ <p><font size="+1">Aeka<br>Level 60 Paladin on Povar<br><font color="#cc00cc">Just don't ask about the purple hair</font></font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukeynsoulfighter.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Keyn Soulfighter</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 273<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/7/02 11:27:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=161.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://jbob147.homestead.com/files/bar.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: *stumble* *bump* *crash* *thud*</span><hr size=1> im a half elf.... so i dont really have that problem.. although it gets really hard to see sometimes..<br><br>recently i added something to my armor that gives off light.... unbeknowst to me what it is though.<br><br>if you're just in a dark place traveling, as opposed to fighting, summon a halo of light for yourself... thats what i used to do for my human paladin bud when we were 22 and 18 respectively.<br><br>ro armor has a light effect to it.. maybe not all the peices though..<br><br>and of course... soulfire can lead you through the dark always. <p><font face="verdana" size="1"><p align=center><a HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=18522">My Magelo Profile</a>                                                                   <a href="mailto:wreched_hamlet@hotmail.com">Email</a><br><img src="http://jbob147.homestead.com/files/auron.jpg"><br>You're Auron, Spira's most famous Guardian! Often very cold, you're also very resourceful.<br>You have a very good public image, and its not uncommon for people to look up to you,<br>and even want to be you! You always keep your promises, no matter what.</font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uluthair.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Luthair</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1756<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/7/02 11:27:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=161.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: *stumble* *bump* *crash* *thud*</span><hr size=1> Could just carry a glowing stone band around. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6318"><img src="http://www3.sympatico.ca/lchisholm/luth_sig.jpg" border=0></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=derryk>Derryk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 30<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/7/02 11:48:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=161.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: *stumble* *bump* *crash* *thud*</span><hr size=1> Snow storm mask off of Velk (something like 7ac 5str 9svc 0 wt effect:heat sight) is an option if you aren't wearing something really nice on your face (e.g., eyepatch of plunder) or if you want to just swap it our situationally.  I have no idea of the going rate for it, but I do recall seeing it for sale in EC  once or twice.  I think a lot of people regard it as very mediocre--especially considering the mob it drops from, but I know some human monks (alts) who keep an eye out for this mask.<br><br>I've worn the mask for the last 4-5 months since I was awraded it after we droppped Velk a few times for our casters and I love it.  I can't believe what a difference it makes having infravision vs even a good light source.  Other than the infravision, the mask doesn't have the greatest stats, but you can't beat getting night vision if you don't have it.<br><br>I can only remember the mask dropping one time in the 4 or 5 times I think we killed him though, so I don't know how common it is.<br><br>Being able to find your way around in the dark if you can't&gt;&gt;&gt;stats <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Derryk Morrdayne<br>55 Knight<br>Ayonae Ro<br>Arcturus<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uwhitchywhon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Whitchywhon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 110<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/7/02 1:42:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=161.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: *stumble* *bump* *crash* *thud*</span><hr size=1> I carry around a GLS.<br>I like 